Reviews.Title: great computer
Reviews.Author: rstan
Reviews.Content: what part of locking the mouse pad button when typing do people not understand. How difficult can this be.I have had my 5532 for 7 months and absolutely love it.I have upgraded the cpu to a tl-60 and also have added ram for a total of 4gb. all for about $75, but even with the tf-20 cpu it was pretty good for the money.One thing i have noticed is that a lot of laptops have lowered their prices since about may or june. I think they did it in response to this computer, so looking around would not hurt at this point.I have not had any problems with anything being flimsy or cheaply made, but as it is now august i would suggest looking for a more powerful cpu in the same price range of about $350-400 as they are out there now or installing a tl-60 for about $25 if you do it your self. Note the job can be tedious to anyone that has never taken a laptop apart before, but there are several sites that can be helpful.

Reviews.Title: Price is Great, BUT, Cursor Freezes Frequently!
Reviews.Author: HCS
Reviews.Content: This computer is really cute, has a nice screen, and has adequate RAM if you don't store a lot of photos or documents on it, but has an absolutely horrible cursor issue. The cursor gets stuck and freezes AT LEAST 1x/week! It's awful. I always fear for my documents, and save them every 2 minutes, because the cursor freezes, and I have to restart the computer. In short, I would not purchase this computer again, and I would not recommend it to anyone.

Reviews.Title: Great Computer and Grat Delivery
Reviews.Author: Amazon Customer
Reviews.Content: Great Seller, no fear here.....  Everything just as advertised and delivery was on time

Reviews.Title: so far so good
Reviews.Author: Jappy
Reviews.Content: bought this laptop yesterday, and so far no problems yet.  Internet browsing, email and basic MS Office tasks are adequate for my needs.  I also bought a wireless mouse since the mouse controls on the keyboard seem a bit flimsy.In addition, I deleted the games file (99 mb's) in size and the computer's running faster now.Overall, from my short exposure to it, the laptop is adequate.

Reviews.Title: Don't buy this laptop- or any Acer- in seconds you can google problems
Reviews.Author: D. Mcarthur "Mysonshines"
Reviews.Content: and see that not only are the products very poor quality (our Acer's screen cracked under very little pressure- as so many others have), the links to help for customer service don't work, and the help at the India call center is polite but completely useless. If you purchase an Acer you can't say you haven't been warned.

Reviews.Title: I'd rather get a Toshiba
Reviews.Author: djelrock "djelrock"
Reviews.Content: Bought this for my teenage son 6 months ago. Had trouble with audio in December. Called Acer to find out what to do and they told me I had to ship it back for repairs. I asked them if they could send box and they said shipping is not included in the one year warranty and that I would have to get it to them on my own. Asked them why shipping is not included and they didn't have an answer. Buy at your own risk. Customer Service is terrible as I had difficulty communicating with rep on the other line and who couldn't answer my questions clearly. The information above was gathered after two months of calling and getting hung up on. Terrible service. Computer is expensive enough that you'd think customer service is up to par but no go. Be aware when purchasing this item.

Reviews.Title: No WebCam or Mic
Reviews.Author: MightyMe
Reviews.Content: My father bought this laptop for its exceptional price-to-features ratio.  One of the reasons he purchased this is because it has both an integrated MIC and WebCam so that we might Skype together.  Unfortunately, these features, though physically there, they DO NOT WORK.After some time researching this, apparently, no one else finds these features to work either.  And further, there is no real documentation to indicate why.I would NOT recommend this laptop on principle as I believe this to be a bait-n-switch tactic, where Acer put features on the back of the box, and hoped customers wouldn't notice the difference.  :-/Pay a little more for a different machine, and get what you pay for.

Reviews.Title: CHEAP LAPTOP
Reviews.Author: Übermensch
Reviews.Content: My title sums it up.  It's cheap in every way.Worst trackpad ever.  That's not true.  My girlfriend's $800 Toshiba has a worse trackpad, but this one is still terrible.  As I write this review it will suddenly select a part of the paragraph up a couple lines and I'll find myself typing in the middle of where I already was typing.  Argh!!That's not the worst part.  Every time I wake this computer from sleep, it is 100X slower than before.  It is so bad that if I ever accidentally put it to sleep (like, close the lid), I just hold down the power key and restart it.  It's unusably slow after sleep... like the processor never fully cycles-up after sleep mode.  But if it never goes to sleep (I've changed the settings so when it is plugged in it never goes to sleep) it is fine.  I'm trying to contact Acer "Technical Support", which so far has been an oxy-moron.  Typical of PCs but I believe Acer is one of the worst in this department.This is on a brand-new computer.  No porn, no spyware, no programs installed by me except iTunes.Cough up the dough and get a Mac.  If you can't afford one, suffer with something like this?I bought it as a present for my Mother but now I kinda feel bad about it.  And I dread the phone calls I'm about to get about "this and that doesn't work blah blah blah".

Reviews.Title: Happy
Reviews.Author: Andrew Suhr
Reviews.Content: I got the computer in the time frame promised and it works as expected. Just the experience I was looking for.
